The paper discusses the design of a replicated data store that provides causal consistency, which is a topic that falls under the distributed computing (cs.DC) and database (cs.DB) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the trade-off between conflicting requirements, which is a topic that falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes an adaptive approach, which is a topic that falls under the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
